  <p>As before, with a matched pairs design we will focus on the differences in responses. First, we need an appropriate way to organize the data. We can do this with a two-way table looking at the two variables measured on each children – whether or not woke up to mom's voice and whether or not woke up to the conventional alarm.</p>
  
