      <p>Another aspect of this same study considered not just whether the child woke up but whether he/she successfully escaped from the house within 5 minutes of the alarm sounding. The article reports that 20 children escaped when they heard the mother's voice, and only 9 escaped when they heard the conventional tone.</p>
